12/12/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police detained former Deputy Interior Minister Tomislav Mercep on Friday (December 10th) during an investigation of war crimes committed against Serb civilians during the 1991-1995 war. According to local media, police units under his command were allegedly involved in illegal detention, torture and killings of Serbs in Zagreb and Pakrac in 1991. (HRT, Croatian Times, DPA, AP - 10/12/10) 
